latestPosts.caption: Frustrated with having to constantly say no and then deal with the arguments and negotiation around it - I came up with this system with my kids… it’s been 2 months now and it’s worked brilliantly! Hence sharing after having tried and tested it .. it’s gamified parenting at its best and I hope it helps you as well!

Tbh, I would never ever weigh myself at night - no matter what. 

Do you binge eat or crave sweet at night?

Sharing this as a reminder to move no matter what the weather holds 

I posted this at 6 pm a few days ago on my stories and got so many messages saying it’s raining just eat vada pav or put your feet up.. I had seen a spot of sunshine and gotten ready.. but the moment it rained I (took a pic and then) changed and rushed down to do 90 mins of weights instead .. 

Some things we can’t control (as much as I wish we could) but what you can control is what you do with it… 

Also sharing this cause my new outfit went waste - why lie 😂❤️

Who else saves clothes from the donation pile - incase you need them on holiday? (And then don’t wear them on holiday…) 

On our way back home.. with 4 suitcases this size filled with stuff we didn’t need on vacation and more things we won’t need back home 🙈🙈

Day 6 and 7 included 2 trips back at @megaadventuresingapore for climbing and zip lining! The kids really loved this! There was a quick jump too.. 
we got a few rounds on the @skylinelugesingapore too and a little shopping for sports wear … our favorite :) 

Some beach time and delicious meals @haidilaosingapore and @dintaifungsg .. 
do you guys want a list of things to do in SG with kids?
